25 HB 54/SCSFA
SENATE SUBSTITUTE TO HB 54
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Titles 16, 31, 43, and 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 crimes and offenses, health, professions and businesses, and revenue and taxation,
3 respectively, so as to authorize advanced practice registered nurses and physician assistants
4 to order home healthcare services to patients of home health agencies; to provide for
5 definitions; to provide for the approval of continuing education regarding death certificates;
6 to provide for authorizing job descriptions; to provide for tax credits for qualified caregiving
7 expenses to include advanced practice registered nurses and physician assistants; to provide
8 for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
10 SECTION 1.
11 Title 16 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to crimes and offenses, is
12 amended by revising paragraph (4.2) of Code Section 16-13-72, relating to the sale,
13 distribution, or possession of dangerous drugs, as follows:
14 "(4.2) A registered professional nurse licensed under Article 1 of Chapter 26 of Title 43
15 who is employed or engaged by a licensed home health agency may possess sterile saline,
16 sterile water, and diluted heparin for use as intravenous maintenance for use in a home
17 health setting, and such nurse may administer such items to patients of the home health
