108 SECTION 4.
109 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 31-7-153, relating to standards for
110 patient care and agency operation, regulations as to issuance, denial, suspension, or
111 revocation of licenses, and hearings, as follows:
112 "31-7-153.
113 The department shall promulgate regulations which define standards for the care, treatment,
114 health, safety, welfare, and comfort of patients served by home health agencies and for the
115 maintenance and operation of home health agencies which will promote safe and adequate
116 care and treatment of the patients. These regulations shall be no less stringent than those
117 required for participation of home health agencies in the Title XVIII medicare Medicare
118 program and shall include, but not be limited to, a provision requiring the agency to have
119 policies established by a professional group which includes at least one physician and one
120 registered nurse and appropriate representation from other professional disciplines;
121 provisions governing the services the agency provides; provisions for the supervision of
122 services by a physician, advanced practice registered nurse, physician assistant, or
